      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**V1 Compute Provision Endpoint**\n\n### Overview\n\nThe `/v1/compute/provision` endpoint provides a programmable interface for provisioning virtual machines on CloudNexus. This endpoint supports the creation of new virtual machines based on user-provided specifications.\n\n### HTTP Method\n\n* **POST**: This operation creates a new virtual machine instance.\n\n### Request Parameters\n\nThe following constraints apply to the request body:\n\n| Parameter | Required | Data Type | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `instance_type` | Yes | String | The size of the VM to provision (e.g., t2.micro, c4.xlarge). Required. |\n| `region` | Yes | String | The cloud region for deployment. Required. |\n| `image_id` | Yes | String | The OS image to boot from. Required. |\n\n### Example Request Body\n\n```json\n{\n  \"instance_type\": \"t2.micro\",\n  \"region\": \"us-west-2\",\n  \"image_id\": \"c03e1078-510e-4444-94ec-f46a87c4bdf1\"\n}\n```\n\n### Response\n\nThe response to a successful request will be a `201 Created` status code",
      "source": "target",
